Police spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbhele confirmed that Nottingham Road police arrested a 43-year-old suspect."He will be charged for murder kidnapping and house robbery. He will appear in the Howick Magistrates Court on 3 March 2017 " she said."Further information cannot be revealed at this stage as the investigation is continuing " Mbhele added.Christine and Roger Solik were kidnapped from the home in a Nottingham Road estate two weeks ago. Their bodies were found in a river in Impendle nearly 70 kilometers from their home.- TMG Digital/TimesLIVE